  "prompt": "What are the best places to eat vegetarian food in New Delhi?",
  "response": "Delhi is a vegetarian paradise! You'll find incredible options across all price ranges. Here are some of the best places to eat vegetarian food in New Delhi, categorized for easier browsing:\n\n**Fine Dining/Upscale:**\n\n*   **Indian Accent (The Lodhi):**  Considered one of the best restaurants in India, they have a fantastic vegetarian tasting menu that showcases modern Indian cuisine.  Expensive but worth the splurge for a special occasion.\n*   **Masala Library by Jiggs Kalra (Connaught Place):** Another excellent choice for modern Indian cuisine with innovative vegetarian dishes.  A bit more expensive but offers a memorable culinary experience.\n*   **Set'z (DLF Emporio):** Features a diverse menu with multiple cuisines including Indian, Asian, and Western. They have plenty of vegetarian options, especially within their Indian and Asian sections. Good ambiance and excellent service.\n*   **Varq (The Taj Mahal Hotel):** A sophisticated restaurant serving modern Indian cuisine with a focus on presentation and quality ingredients.  They have a well-crafted vegetarian menu.\n*   **Indian Accent at Home (Delivery Only):** For a luxurious meal delivered to your doorstep, Indian Accent also offers a home delivery service with a curated vegetarian menu.\n\n**Mid-Range Restaurants:**\n\n*   **Gulati Restaurant (Pandara Road Market):** A Delhi institution known for its North Indian and Mughlai cuisine. While famous for its butter chicken, their vegetarian dishes like Dal Makhani, Shahi Paneer, and Malai Kofta are outstanding.\n*   **Sagar Ratna (Multiple Locations):** A very popular chain for authentic South Indian vegetarian food. Their dosas, idlis, vadas, and uttapams are consistently good.  Great value for money.\n*   **Haldiram's (Multiple Locations):** A ubiquitous chain offering a wide variety of vegetarian Indian snacks, sweets, and meals.  Reliable, affordable, and a good place for a quick bite.\n*   **Bikanerwala (Multiple Locations):** Similar to Haldiram's, offering a wide array of Indian vegetarian dishes and sweets. Clean, efficient, and budget-friendly.\n*   **Saravana Bhavan (Connaught Place):** Another excellent South Indian restaurant, known for its traditional and flavorful dishes. Expect a bit of a wait, but it's worth it.\n*   **Rajdhani Thali Restaurant (Multiple Locations):** Specializes in Rajasthani and Gujarati thalis, offering a wide variety of vegetarian dishes in an unlimited format.  A great way to sample different regional flavors.\n*   **Carnatic Cafe (New Friends Colony):** Authentic South Indian with a focus on the cuisine of Bangalore (Karnataka). Try their Benne Masala Dosa.  Popular and often crowded.\n\n**Budget-Friendly/Street Food:**\n\n*   **Parathe Wali Gali (Chandni Chowk):**  A narrow lane in Old Delhi famous for its parathas (stuffed flatbreads).  Many different fillings are available, mostly vegetarian. Be prepared for the crowds and the experience!\n*   **Shree Shyam Bhandar (Chawri Bazar):** Famous for its bedmi aloo (a flavorful potato curry served with fried bread). A Delhi institution.\n*   **Shiv Tikki Wala (Multiple Locations):** Offers delicious and affordable aloo tikki (potato patties) and other street food snacks.\n*   **Dahi Bhalla Corner (Chandni Chowk):**  Try their dahi bhalla (lentil fritters in yogurt sauce) for a refreshing and flavorful snack.\n*   **Bittu Tikki Wala (Multiple Locations):** A popular street food chain offering various snacks, including tikkis, chaats, and gol gappe.\n*   **Kake di Hatti (Chandni Chowk):** This is a very old, no-frills eatery known for its North Indian veg dishes such as dal makhani, shahi paneer and malai kofta. The portion size is pretty big and can be shared between 2-3 people.\n\n**Specific Recommendations & Tips:**\n\n*   **For a unique experience:** Try the vegetarian tasting menu at Indian Accent.\n*   **For South Indian food:** Sagar Ratna, Saravana Bhavan, and Carnatic Cafe are excellent choices.\n*   **For a quick and affordable meal:** Haldiram's and Bikanerwala are reliable options.\n*   **For a traditional Rajasthani/Gujarati thali:** Rajdhani Thali Restaurant is a great choice.\n*   **For street food:** Explore Chandni Chowk, but be mindful of hygiene and opt for vendors that appear clean and busy.\n*   **Don't be afraid to ask:** Many restaurants have hidden vegetarian gems. Ask your server for recommendations.\n*   **Be aware of Jain options:** If you're strictly vegetarian (Jain), specify your dietary requirements, as some restaurants may use ingredients like onion and garlic.\n*   **Order the Dal Makhani and Paneer Tikka Masala**: These are two staples in North Indian veg cuisine, and you'll find many places in Delhi that have perfected this dish.\n\nEnjoy your culinary adventure in Delhi! You'll be amazed by the variety and deliciousness of the vegetarian food on offer.\n",
